# PDF.js CMaps + standard fonts for the in-browser PDF preview.
#
# These are copied from `node_modules/pdfjs-dist/{cmaps,standard_fonts}` by
# `scripts/copy-pdfjs-assets.mjs`, which runs automatically on `npm install`
# (see `postinstall` in package.json). Re-run manually with:
#   node scripts/copy-pdfjs-assets.mjs
#
# They are required so pdf.js can decode CJK fonts (Adobe-GB1 / Adobe-CNS1 /
# Adobe-Japan1 / Adobe-Korea1) embedded in source PDFs — without them, every
# Chinese character in an uploaded PDF renders as blank / a square.
#
# We intentionally don't commit them: ~1.85 MB of binary blobs that would
# bloat the repo and re-appear in every diff after a pdfjs-dist upgrade.

cmaps/
standard_fonts/

# Always commit this .gitignore so the directory exists in fresh clones.
!.gitignore
